The paper deals with the problem of computing shortest paths in a geometric domain, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of data structures and algorithms to solve this problem also makes it relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the complexity of the algorithm, which falls under the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of computing shortest paths in a geometric domain also has applications in graphics and visualization (cs.GR) and scientific computing (cs.SC).
